title: Tech
description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from Tech, skipping any feeds with errors.

items.title: Monarch Tractor preps for layoffs and warns employees it may ‘shut down’
items.description: The memo that went out Thursday, which TechCrunch obtained, says the "timing" of the company's pivot away from tractor manufacturing puts it at risk.

items.title: Uber Eats will use Starship sidewalk robots to deliver food in the UK
items.description: The two companies will start in the UK this year, before expanding to other European cities in 2026 and the U.S. in 2027.

items.title: Trump Takes Aim at State AI Laws in Draft Executive Order
items.description: The draft order, obtained by WIRED, instructs the US Justice Department to sue states that pass laws regulating AI.

items.title: Google DeepMind Hires Former CTO of Boston Dynamics as the Company Pushes Deeper Into Robotics

items.title: NASA Finally Weighs In on the Origin of 3I/ATLAS
items.description: After weeks of silence, NASA has officially dismissed speculation that 3I/ATLAS has anything to do with aliens.

items.title: Cavela lands $6.6M to help brands beat pre-tariff manufacturing costs
items.description: The startup claims that its AI agents can reduce the cost of product manufacturing by an average of 35%.

items.title: Nvidia’s record $57B revenue and upbeat forecast quiets AI bubble talk
items.description: Nvidia's earnings were dominated by its data center business.
